## Objective

Extend the ExtensionManifestSchema in `packages/extension-api/src/manifest-schema.ts` to support server-side extension capabilities and declarative proxy configuration. Also add the new fields to the `ExtensionRecord` and `ExtensionRecordPublic` types in `packages/extension-api/src/types.ts`.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Update manifest-schema.ts

Add three new Zod schemas and integrate them into the existing `ExtensionManifestSchema` in `packages/extension-api/src/manifest-schema.ts`:

```typescript
import { z } from 'zod';

/** Declares a secret an extension needs (e.g., an API key). */
const SecretDeclarationSchema = z.object({
  /** Secret key name (lowercase snake_case). */
  key: z.string().regex(/^[a-z][a-z0-9_]*$/),
  /** Human-readable label for the settings UI. */
  label: z.string().min(1),
  /** Help text shown in the settings UI. */
  description: z.string().optional(),
  /** Whether the extension cannot function without this secret. */
  required: z.boolean().default(false),
});

/** Declarative proxy configuration for zero-code API passthrough (Tier 1). */
const DataProxySchema = z.object({
  /** Base URL of the upstream API. */
  baseUrl: z.string().url(),
  /** HTTP header name for the auth credential. */
  authHeader: z.string().default('Authorization'),
  /** How the secret value is formatted in the header. */
  authType: z.enum(['Bearer', 'Basic', 'Token', 'Custom']).default('Bearer'),
  /** Key name in the extension's secret store to use for auth. */
  authSecret: z.string(),
  /** Optional path rewriting rules (from -> to). */
  pathRewrite: z.record(z.string(), z.string()).optional(),
});

/** Server-side capability declarations for data-provider extensions. */
const ServerCapabilitiesSchema = z.object({
  /** Path to the server entry point relative to extension directory. */
  serverEntry: z.string().default('./server.ts'),
  /** Allowlisted external hosts this extension will contact. */
  externalHosts: z.array(z.string().url()).optional(),
  /** Secrets this extension requires (drives auto-generated settings UI). */
  secrets: z.array(SecretDeclarationSchema).optional(),
});
```

Then add both optional fields to the existing `ExtensionManifestSchema`:

```typescript
export const ExtensionManifestSchema = z.object({
  // ... all existing fields remain unchanged ...
  /** Server-side capability declarations. Present if the extension has server.ts. */
  serverCapabilities: ServerCapabilitiesSchema.optional(),
  /** Declarative proxy config for zero-code API passthrough. */
  dataProxy: DataProxySchema.optional(),
});
```

Export the new types:

```typescript
export type SecretDeclaration = z.infer<typeof SecretDeclarationSchema>;
export type DataProxyConfig = z.infer<typeof DataProxySchema>;
export type ServerCapabilities = z.infer<typeof ServerCapabilitiesSchema>;
```

### 2. Update ExtensionRecord in types.ts

Add server-awareness fields to `ExtensionRecord` in `packages/extension-api/src/types.ts`:

```typescript
export interface ExtensionRecord {
  // ... all existing fields ...
  /** Whether the extension has a server.ts entry point on disk. */
  hasServerEntry: boolean;
  /** Whether the extension has a dataProxy manifest declaration. */
  hasDataProxy: boolean;
  /** Absolute path to the resolved server entry point (if hasServerEntry is true). */
  serverEntryPath?: string;
}
```

Also add to `ExtensionRecordPublic`:

```typescript
export interface ExtensionRecordPublic {
  // ... all existing fields ...
  hasServerEntry: boolean;
  hasDataProxy: boolean;
}
```

### 3. Update barrel exports in index.ts

In `packages/extension-api/src/index.ts`, add exports for the new types:

```typescript
export type { SecretDeclaration, DataProxyConfig, ServerCapabilities } from './manifest-schema.js';
```

### 4. Fix compilation

Update every location that constructs an `ExtensionRecord` to include the new required fields `hasServerEntry: false` and `hasDataProxy: false` as defaults. This includes:
- `extension-discovery.ts` `readExtension()` method (both success and error return paths)
- `extension-manager.ts` `createExtension()` method
- Any test files that construct `ExtensionRecord` objects

Also update `toPublic()` in `extension-manager.ts` to include the new fields.

## Acceptance Criteria

- Existing extensions with no `serverCapabilities` or `dataProxy` parse identically (backward compatible)
- A manifest with `serverCapabilities.secrets` array validates correctly
- A manifest with `dataProxy.baseUrl` and `dataProxy.authSecret` validates correctly
- `SecretDeclaration.key` rejects uppercase characters and keys starting with numbers
- `DataProxySchema.authType` only accepts 'Bearer', 'Basic', 'Token', 'Custom'
- `hasServerEntry` and `hasDataProxy` fields appear on `ExtensionRecord` and `ExtensionRecordPublic`
- All existing extension tests continue to pass (add `hasServerEntry: false, hasDataProxy: false` to test fixtures)
- Add unit tests in `packages/extension-api/src/__tests__/manifest-schema.test.ts` covering: valid serverCapabilities, valid dataProxy, invalid secret key format, missing required fields, backward compat with no new fields

## Objective

Create `packages/shared/src/extension-secrets.ts` implementing an AES-256-GCM encrypted per-extension secret store. Secrets are stored at `{dorkHome}/extension-secrets/{ext-id}.json` with a host key at `{dorkHome}/host.key`.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Create ExtensionSecretStore class

New file: `packages/shared/src/extension-secrets.ts`

```typescript
import { createCipheriv, createDecipheriv, randomBytes, scryptSync } from 'node:crypto';
import { readFile, writeFile, mkdir, chmod } from 'node:fs/promises';
import { join, dirname } from 'node:path';
import { existsSync } from 'node:fs';

const ALGORITHM = 'aes-256-gcm';
const KEY_LENGTH = 32;
const IV_LENGTH = 16;
const AUTH_TAG_LENGTH = 16;
const SALT = 'dorkos-ext-secrets';

/** Per-process cache of the derived encryption key. */
let cachedDerivedKey: Buffer | null = null;
let cachedDorkHome: string | null = null;

/**
 * Encrypted per-extension secret store using AES-256-GCM.
 *
 * Secrets are stored in `{dorkHome}/extension-secrets/{extensionId}.json`.
 * The host key lives at `{dorkHome}/host.key` (mode 0o600).
 * Encryption format: base64(IV[16] || AuthTag[16] || Ciphertext).
 */
export class ExtensionSecretStore {
  private cache: Record<string, string> | null = null;
  private readonly secretsDir: string;
  private readonly secretsFilePath: string;
  private readonly hostKeyPath: string;

  constructor(
    private readonly extensionId: string,
    private readonly dorkHome: string
  ) {
    this.secretsDir = join(dorkHome, 'extension-secrets');
    this.secretsFilePath = join(this.secretsDir, `${extensionId}.json`);
    this.hostKeyPath = join(dorkHome, 'host.key');
  }

  /** Get a secret value by key. Returns null if not set. */
  async get(key: string): Promise<string | null> {
    const secrets = await this.loadSecrets();
    const encrypted = secrets[key];
    if (!encrypted) return null;
    try {
      return this.decrypt(encrypted);
    } catch {
      // Corrupted data — treat as missing
      return null;
    }
  }

  /** Set a secret value. Writes through to disk immediately. */
  async set(key: string, value: string): Promise<void> {
    const secrets = await this.loadSecrets();
    secrets[key] = this.encrypt(value);
    this.cache = secrets;
    await this.saveSecrets(secrets);
  }

  /** Delete a secret. Writes through to disk immediately. */
  async delete(key: string): Promise<void> {
    const secrets = await this.loadSecrets();
    delete secrets[key];
    this.cache = secrets;
    await this.saveSecrets(secrets);
  }

  /** Check if a secret key is set (without decrypting). */
  async has(key: string): Promise<boolean> {
    const secrets = await this.loadSecrets();
    return key in secrets;
  }

  private encrypt(plaintext: string): string {
    const key = this.getDerivedKey();
    const iv = randomBytes(IV_LENGTH);
    const cipher = createCipheriv(ALGORITHM, key, iv);
    const encrypted = Buffer.concat([cipher.update(plaintext, 'utf8'), cipher.final()]);
    const authTag = cipher.getAuthTag();
    // Format: IV[16] || AuthTag[16] || Ciphertext
    return Buffer.concat([iv, authTag, encrypted]).toString('base64');
  }

  private decrypt(encoded: string): string {
    const key = this.getDerivedKey();
    const buf = Buffer.from(encoded, 'base64');
    const iv = buf.subarray(0, IV_LENGTH);
    const authTag = buf.subarray(IV_LENGTH, IV_LENGTH + AUTH_TAG_LENGTH);
    const ciphertext = buf.subarray(IV_LENGTH + AUTH_TAG_LENGTH);
    const decipher = createDecipheriv(ALGORITHM, key, iv);
    decipher.setAuthTag(authTag);
    return decipher.update(ciphertext) + decipher.final('utf8');
  }

  private getDerivedKey(): Buffer {
    if (cachedDerivedKey && cachedDorkHome === this.dorkHome) {
      return cachedDerivedKey;
    }
    const hostKey = this.loadOrCreateHostKey();
    cachedDerivedKey = scryptSync(hostKey, SALT, KEY_LENGTH) as Buffer;
    cachedDorkHome = this.dorkHome;
    return cachedDerivedKey;
  }

  private loadOrCreateHostKey(): Buffer {
    const keyPath = this.hostKeyPath;
    if (existsSync(keyPath)) {
      return require('node:fs').readFileSync(keyPath);
    }
    const key = randomBytes(KEY_LENGTH);
    require('node:fs').mkdirSync(dirname(keyPath), { recursive: true });
    require('node:fs').writeFileSync(keyPath, key, { mode: 0o600 });
    return key;
  }

  private async loadSecrets(): Promise<Record<string, string>> {
    if (this.cache) return this.cache;
    try {
      const data = await readFile(this.secretsFilePath, 'utf-8');
      this.cache = JSON.parse(data) as Record<string, string>;
      return this.cache;
    } catch {
      this.cache = {};
      return this.cache;
    }
  }

  private async saveSecrets(secrets: Record<string, string>): Promise<void> {
    await mkdir(this.secretsDir, { recursive: true });
    const tempPath = this.secretsFilePath + '.tmp';
    await writeFile(tempPath, JSON.stringify(secrets, null, 2), 'utf-8');
    const { rename } = await import('node:fs/promises');
    await rename(tempPath, this.secretsFilePath);
  }
}
```

### 2. Export from shared package

Add the export to `packages/shared/src/index.ts` or the appropriate subpath export. The spec indicates this should be importable as `@dorkos/shared/extension-secrets`. Check the shared package's `package.json` exports map and add:

```json
"./extension-secrets": {
  "types": "./src/extension-secrets.ts",
  "default": "./dist/extension-secrets.js"
}
```

### 3. Export SecretStore interface from extension-api

Create `packages/extension-api/src/server-extension-api.ts` with the `SecretStore` interface and `DataProviderContext` interface (the full context factory will be built in Phase 2, but the types are needed now for the secret store to implement):

```typescript
/** Encrypted per-extension secret store. */
export interface SecretStore {
  get(key: string): Promise<string | null>;
  set(key: string, value: string): Promise<void>;
  delete(key: string): Promise<void>;
  has(key: string): Promise<boolean>;
}

/** Context injected into server-side extension code. */
export interface DataProviderContext {
  readonly secrets: SecretStore;
  readonly storage: {
    loadData<T = unknown>(): Promise<T | null>;
    saveData<T = unknown>(data: T): Promise<void>;
  };
  schedule(intervalSeconds: number, fn: () => Promise<void>): () => void;
  emit(event: string, data: unknown): void;
  readonly extensionId: string;
  readonly extensionDir: string;
}

/** Server-side extension entry point signature. */
export type ServerExtensionRegister = (
  router: import('express').Router,
  ctx: DataProviderContext
) => void | (() => void) | Promise<void | (() => void)>;
```

Add to `packages/extension-api/package.json` exports:

```json
"./server": {
  "types": "./src/server-extension-api.ts",
  "default": "./dist/server-extension-api.js"
}
```

Export types from a barrel or directly.

## Testing

Create `packages/shared/src/__tests__/extension-secrets.test.ts`:

- **Roundtrip**: `set('key', 'value')` then `get('key')` returns `'value'`
- **Missing key**: `get('nonexistent')` returns `null`
- **has()**: returns `true` after set, `false` after delete
- **delete()**: `set` then `delete` then `get` returns `null`
- **Isolation**: Store for extension-a cannot read secrets from extension-b (different file paths)
- **Host key generation**: On first access in a fresh dorkHome, `host.key` file is created
- **Host key permissions**: The `host.key` file has mode `0o600` (owner read/write only)
- **Corrupted data**: If the encrypted value is tampered with, `get()` returns `null` instead of throwing
- **Atomic writes**: Verify the secrets file is written via temp file + rename

Use a temp directory (`os.tmpdir()`) for `dorkHome` in tests. Clean up after each test.

## Acceptance Criteria

- ExtensionSecretStore encrypts secrets with AES-256-GCM
- Host key auto-generates on first use with 0o600 permissions
- Per-extension isolation via separate JSON files
- Corrupted encrypted data returns null (does not throw)
- Derived key is cached per-process (scryptSync called only once)
- All tests pass

## Objective

Update `ExtensionDiscovery` in `apps/server/src/services/extensions/extension-discovery.ts` to detect the presence of `server.ts` (or `server.js`) alongside `index.ts` in extension directories, and populate the `hasServerEntry`, `hasDataProxy`, and `serverEntryPath` fields on `ExtensionRecord`.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Update readExtension() in extension-discovery.ts

After successfully parsing the manifest, check for a server entry point:

```typescript
private async readExtension(
  extDir: string,
  dirName: string,
  scope: 'global' | 'local'
): Promise<ExtensionRecord> {
  // ... existing manifest parsing code ...

  // After successful manifest parse:
  const manifest = result.data;
  const serverEntryRel = manifest.serverCapabilities?.serverEntry ?? './server.ts';
  const resolvedServerEntry = path.join(extDir, serverEntryRel);

  let hasServerEntry = false;
  try {
    await fs.access(resolvedServerEntry);
    hasServerEntry = true;
  } catch {
    // Also check for .js variant
    try {
      await fs.access(resolvedServerEntry.replace(/\.ts$/, '.js'));
      hasServerEntry = true;
    } catch {
      // No server entry point
    }
  }

  const hasDataProxy = !!manifest.dataProxy;

  return {
    id: result.data.id,
    manifest: result.data,
    status: 'discovered',
    scope,
    path: extDir,
    bundleReady: false,
    hasServerEntry,
    hasDataProxy,
    serverEntryPath: hasServerEntry ? resolvedServerEntry : undefined,
  };
}
```

### 2. Update error return paths

Both error return paths in `readExtension()` must also include the new fields with default values:

```typescript
return {
  // ... existing error fields ...
  hasServerEntry: false,
  hasDataProxy: false,
};
```

### 3. Update logging

Enhance the discovery log line to indicate server-capable extensions:

```typescript
logger.info(
  `[Extensions] Discovered ${results.length} extension(s): ${results.map((r) => {
    const flags = [r.status];
    if (r.hasServerEntry) flags.push('server');
    if (r.hasDataProxy) flags.push('proxy');
    return `${r.id} (${flags.join(', ')})`;
  }).join(', ') || 'none'}`
);
```

## Testing

Update or create tests in `apps/server/src/services/extensions/__tests__/extension-discovery.test.ts`:

- **No server.ts**: Extension directory with only `extension.json` + `index.ts` has `hasServerEntry: false`
- **With server.ts**: Extension directory containing `server.ts` has `hasServerEntry: true` and `serverEntryPath` set
- **With server.js**: Extension directory containing `server.js` (pre-compiled) has `hasServerEntry: true`
- **Custom serverEntry**: Manifest with `serverCapabilities.serverEntry: './src/server.ts'` resolves to correct path
- **dataProxy detection**: Manifest with `dataProxy` field has `hasDataProxy: true`
- **Both capabilities**: Extension with both `server.ts` and `dataProxy` has both flags true
- **Backward compat**: Existing extensions without serverCapabilities parse with `hasServerEntry: false, hasDataProxy: false`

Use temp directories with minimal extension fixtures for each test case.

## Acceptance Criteria

- `hasServerEntry` is true when server.ts or server.js exists in the extension directory
- `hasDataProxy` is true when the manifest contains a `dataProxy` field
- `serverEntryPath` is set to the absolute path of the server entry when present
- Custom `serverCapabilities.serverEntry` paths are resolved correctly
- Error/invalid extension records have both new fields set to false
- All existing discovery tests continue to pass

## Objective

Add a `compileServer()` method to `ExtensionCompiler` in `apps/server/src/services/extensions/extension-compiler.ts` that compiles `server.ts` extension code with esbuild targeting Node.js (CJS format for dynamic `require()` loading).

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Add compileServer() method

Add this method to the `ExtensionCompiler` class in `apps/server/src/services/extensions/extension-compiler.ts`:

```typescript
/**
 * Compile a server-side extension entry point for Node.js.
 *
 * Uses CJS format for dynamic require() loading. Externals include express
 * and extension-api packages (provided by the host process).
 *
 * @param record - Extension record with serverEntryPath
 * @returns Compiled code and hash on success, or error on failure
 */
async compileServer(
  record: ExtensionRecord
): Promise<
  { code: string; sourceHash: string } | { error: CompilationError; sourceHash: string }
> {
  if (!record.serverEntryPath) {
    return {
      error: {
        code: 'compilation_failed',
        message: 'No server entry point found',
        errors: [{ text: 'Extension has no serverEntryPath' }],
      },
      sourceHash: '',
    };
  }

  const source = await fs.readFile(record.serverEntryPath, 'utf-8');
  const sourceHash = this.computeSourceHash(source);

  return this.handleServerCompilation(record.id, record.serverEntryPath, sourceHash);
}
```

### 2. Add handleServerCompilation() private method

This follows the same cache hit/miss pattern as `handleCompilation()` but uses the `server/` subdirectory in cache and different esbuild options:

```typescript
/** Handle server-side TypeScript compilation with cache. */
private async handleServerCompilation(
  extId: string,
  entryPath: string,
  sourceHash: string
): Promise<
  { code: string; sourceHash: string } | { error: CompilationError; sourceHash: string }
> {
  const serverCacheDir = path.join(this.cacheDir, 'server');
  await fs.mkdir(serverCacheDir, { recursive: true });

  const cachedJsPath = path.join(serverCacheDir, `${extId}.${sourceHash}.js`);
  const cachedErrorPath = path.join(serverCacheDir, `${extId}.${sourceHash}.error.json`);

  // Cache hit: compiled JS
  try {
    await fs.access(cachedJsPath);
    const cached = await fs.readFile(cachedJsPath, 'utf-8');
    logger.debug(`[Extensions] Server cache hit for ${extId} (${sourceHash})`);
    return { code: cached, sourceHash };
  } catch {
    // Cache miss
  }

  // Cache hit: previous compilation error
  try {
    await fs.access(cachedErrorPath);
    const cachedError = JSON.parse(
      await fs.readFile(cachedErrorPath, 'utf-8')
    ) as CompilationError;
    logger.debug(`[Extensions] Server cached error for ${extId} (${sourceHash})`);
    return { error: cachedError, sourceHash };
  } catch {
    // Cache miss — compile
  }

  return this.runServerEsbuild(extId, entryPath, sourceHash, cachedJsPath, cachedErrorPath);
}
```

### 3. Add runServerEsbuild() private method

Key differences from the client-side `runEsbuild()`: `platform: 'node'`, `target: 'node20'`, `format: 'cjs'`, and different externals.

```typescript
/** Run esbuild for server-side extension code and cache the result. */
private async runServerEsbuild(
  extId: string,
  entryPath: string,
  sourceHash: string,
  cachedJsPath: string,
  cachedErrorPath: string
): Promise<
  { code: string; sourceHash: string } | { error: CompilationError; sourceHash: string }
> {
  try {
    const result = await build({
      entryPoints: [entryPath],
      bundle: true,
      format: 'cjs',
      platform: 'node',
      target: 'node20',
      external: ['express', '@dorkos/extension-api', '@dorkos/extension-api/server'],
      write: false,
      minify: false,
      sourcemap: 'inline',
      logLevel: 'silent',
      loader: { '.ts': 'tsx' },
    });

    const code = result.outputFiles?.[0]?.text ?? '';

    const sizeKb = Buffer.byteLength(code, 'utf-8') / 1024;
    if (sizeKb > BUNDLE_SIZE_WARNING_KB) {
      logger.warn(
        `[Extensions] Server bundle for ${extId} is ${sizeKb.toFixed(0)}KB (exceeds ${BUNDLE_SIZE_WARNING_KB}KB guideline)`
      );
    }

    await fs.writeFile(cachedJsPath, code, 'utf-8');
    try {
      await fs.unlink(cachedErrorPath);
    } catch {
      /* no stale error */
    }

    logger.info(`[Extensions] Compiled server bundle for ${extId} (${sizeKb.toFixed(1)}KB)`);
    return { code, sourceHash };
  } catch (err) {
    const esbuildErr = err as {
      errors?: Array<{
        text: string;
        location?: { file: string; line: number; column: number };
      }>;
    };

    const compilationError: CompilationError = {
      code: 'compilation_failed',
      message: `Server compilation failed for ${extId}`,
      errors: esbuildErr.errors?.map((e) => ({
        text: e.text,
        location: e.location
          ? { file: e.location.file, line: e.location.line, column: e.location.column }
          : undefined,
      })) ?? [{ text: err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Unknown compilation error' }],
    };

    await fs.writeFile(cachedErrorPath, JSON.stringify(compilationError, null, 2), 'utf-8');
    logger.error(
      `[Extensions] Server compilation failed for ${extId}: ${compilationError.errors[0]?.text}`
    );
    return { error: compilationError, sourceHash };
  }
}
```

### 4. Update cleanStaleCache()

Update `cleanStaleCache()` to also clean the `server/` subdirectory:

```typescript
async cleanStaleCache(): Promise<number> {
  let cleaned = 0;
  for (const subDir of [this.cacheDir, path.join(this.cacheDir, 'server')]) {
    try {
      await fs.access(subDir);
    } catch {
      continue;
    }
    const entries = await fs.readdir(subDir);
    for (const entry of entries) {
      const filePath = path.join(subDir, entry);
      try {
        const stat = await fs.stat(filePath);
        if (stat.isFile() && Date.now() - stat.atimeMs > STALE_THRESHOLD_MS) {
          await fs.unlink(filePath);
          cleaned++;
        }
      } catch {
        // Skip
      }
    }
  }
  if (cleaned > 0) {
    logger.info(`[Extensions] Cleaned ${cleaned} stale cache entries`);
  }
  return cleaned;
}
```

## Testing

Add tests in `apps/server/src/services/extensions/__tests__/extension-compiler.test.ts`:

- **Valid server.ts**: Compiles a simple `export default function register(router, ctx) { router.get('/test', ...); }` and returns `{ code, sourceHash }`
- **Invalid TypeScript**: Returns `{ error }` with `code: 'compilation_failed'`
- **No server entry**: Returns error when `record.serverEntryPath` is undefined
- **Cache hit**: Second call with same source returns cached result without recompilation
- **Cache miss on change**: Modified source produces different sourceHash and recompiles
- **Server cache isolation**: Server bundles cached in `server/` subdirectory, not mixed with client bundles
- **CJS format**: Compiled output uses `module.exports` / `exports.default` (CJS, not ESM)
- **Node target**: Compiled output does not include browser polyfills

Use temp directories and minimal TypeScript fixtures.

## Acceptance Criteria

- `compileServer()` produces CJS bundles targeting Node.js 20
- Server bundles cached in `{cacheDir}/server/{extId}.{hash}.js`
- Express and extension-api packages are externalized (not bundled)
- Cache hit/miss logic mirrors the existing client-side pattern
- `cleanStaleCache()` cleans both client and server cache directories
- All existing compiler tests continue to pass

## Objective

Add PUT/GET/DELETE endpoints for per-extension secret management to the extensions router in `apps/server/src/routes/extensions.ts`. These endpoints allow the settings UI to store API keys securely without ever returning the actual secret values.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Import ExtensionSecretStore

At the top of `apps/server/src/routes/extensions.ts`:

```typescript
import { ExtensionSecretStore } from '@dorkos/shared/extension-secrets';
```

### 2. Add Zod validation schema

```typescript
const SetSecretBodySchema = z.object({
  value: z.string().min(1),
});
```

### 3. Add three new route handlers

Add these inside `createExtensionsRouter()` before the `return router;` statement:

```typescript
// GET /api/extensions/:id/secrets -- List declared secrets with isSet status (never returns values)
router.get('/:id/secrets', async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const { id } = req.params;
    if (!SAFE_EXT_ID.test(id)) return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid extension ID' });

    const record = extensionManager.get(id);
    if (!record) {
      return res.status(404).json({ error: `Extension '${id}' not found` });
    }

    const declared = record.manifest.serverCapabilities?.secrets ?? [];
    const store = new ExtensionSecretStore(id, dorkHome);
    const result = await Promise.all(
      declared.map(async (s) => ({
        key: s.key,
        label: s.label,
        description: s.description,
        required: s.required ?? false,
        isSet: await store.has(s.key),
      }))
    );

    res.json(result);
  } catch (err) {
    logger.error(`[Extensions] Failed to list secrets for ${req.params.id}`, err);
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to list secrets' });
  }
});

// PUT /api/extensions/:id/secrets/:key -- Set a secret value (write-only)
router.put('/:id/secrets/:key', async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const { id, key } = req.params;
    if (!SAFE_EXT_ID.test(id)) return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid extension ID' });

    const parsed = SetSecretBodySchema.safeParse(req.body);
    if (!parsed.success) {
      return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Validation failed', details: parsed.error.flatten() });
    }

    const record = extensionManager.get(id);
    if (!record) {
      return res.status(404).json({ error: `Extension '${id}' not found` });
    }

    // Validate key is declared in manifest
    const declared = record.manifest.serverCapabilities?.secrets ?? [];
    if (!declared.some((s) => s.key === key)) {
      return res.status(400).json({ error: `Secret '${key}' not declared in extension manifest` });
    }

    const store = new ExtensionSecretStore(id, dorkHome);
    await store.set(key, parsed.data.value);
    res.json({ ok: true });
  } catch (err) {
    logger.error(`[Extensions] Failed to set secret for ${req.params.id}`, err);
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to set secret' });
  }
});

// DELETE /api/extensions/:id/secrets/:key -- Remove a secret
router.delete('/:id/secrets/:key', async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const { id, key } = req.params;
    if (!SAFE_EXT_ID.test(id)) return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid extension ID' });

    const record = extensionManager.get(id);
    if (!record) {
      return res.status(404).json({ error: `Extension '${id}' not found` });
    }

    const store = new ExtensionSecretStore(id, dorkHome);
    await store.delete(key);
    res.json({ ok: true });
  } catch (err) {
    logger.error(`[Extensions] Failed to delete secret for ${req.params.id}`, err);
    res.status(500).json({ error: 'Failed to delete secret' });
  }
});
