app.use('/api/ext', extDelegationRouter);
```

This must be added after the existing `/api/extensions` mount, and after the `extensionManager` is created.

### 3. SSE events for extensions

Extension SSE events are delivered via the existing unified SSE stream at `/api/events` (via `EventFanOut`). The `ctx.emit()` call in the factory (task 2.1) already uses `eventFanOut.broadcast()` with `ext:{id}:{event}` naming. No new SSE endpoint is needed — clients subscribe to the unified stream and filter by event name.

This approach respects the HTTP/1.1 connection limit (max 6 concurrent connections per origin). The spec's Open Question #2 confirmed this approach.

